A FIFTH pupil has died after spending 12 days in hospital following a car accident on the first day of school.Grade 11 pupil Ndumiso Mkhwanazi (16), from Sivananda Technical High School in KwaMashu, north of Durban, died in King Edward VIII Hospital on Monday night.His sad grandfather, Mandla Nduli (48), said he thought Ndumiso was going to survive.&ldquo;We were shocked when were told he had died. &ldquo;I thought he was going to be alright because his life was in the doctors&rsquo; hands. &ldquo;But it turns out his injuries were more severe than we thought.&rdquo;Ndumiso was injured on the first day of school when a taxi he was travelling in collided with a bus in Ntuzuma, north of Durban.Four pupils died at the scene while another eleven others sustained serious injuries.Mandla said Ndumiso was looking forward to going back to school.&ldquo;The last time we spoke was the night before he went back to school. &ldquo;He told me he wanted to finish high school and study further like his brothers,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;He wanted to be a doctor. &ldquo;I even imagined him wearing the white coat worn by doctors. &ldquo;Now that will never happen.&rdquo;He said he hoped cops would handle the case properly as innocent lives had been lost.&ldquo;These children were looking forward to starting the school year. &ldquo;But now they&rsquo;re gone because of a driver who did not follow the rules of the road.&rdquo; KZN police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said the driver faces five counts of culpable homicide. &ldquo;The cause of the accident is still under investigation.&rdquo;